      <h1 class='title'>Private Sector Treatment</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 16 September 2004 vol 424 c1762WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_1762ws' title='Col. 1762WS &mdash; HC Deb 16 September 2004 vol 424 c1762WS' name='column_1762ws' href='#column_1762ws' rel='bookmark'>1762WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0424P2_20040916_CWS2_618'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-bob-russell' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0424P2_20040916_CWS2_618' title='Link to this speech by Mr Bob Russell' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-bob-russell" title="Mr Bob Russell">Bob Russell</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para">To ask the Secretary of State for Health whether there are medical conditions which the national health service will not treat if the patient has previously paid for the same treatment in the private sector. [188932]</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0424P2_20040916_CWS2_619'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-john-hutton' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0424P2_20040916_CWS2_619' title='Link to this speech by Mr John Hutton' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-john-hutton" title="Mr John Hutton">Mr. Hutton</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para">The national health service would generally pay for any treatment that a patient had previously received as a private patient, so long as it is a treatment normally provided by the NHS and there is appropriate clinical approval.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
